quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  31,1,"Alif-Lam-Meem. (Alphabets of the Arabic language – Allah, and to whomever He reveals, know their precise meanings.)"
  31,2,"These are verses of the wise Book."
  31,3,"Guidance and mercy for the righteous."
  31,4,"Those who keep the prayer established and pay the charity and accept faith in the Hereafter."
  31,5,"It is they who are on guidance from their Lord, and only they are the successful."
  31,6,"And some people buy words of play, in order to mislead from Allah’s path, without knowledge; and to make it an article of mockery; for them is a disgraceful punishment."
  31,7,"And when Our verses are recited to him he haughtily turns away as if he did not hear them – as if there is deafness in his ears; so give him the glad tidings of a painful punishment."
  31,8,"Indeed those who believed and did good deeds – for them are Gardens of serenity."
  31,9,"In which they will abide; it is a true promise of Allah; and only He is the Almighty, the Wise."
  31,10,"He created the heavens without any supports visible to you, and cast mountains as anchors into the earth so that it may not shake with you, and spread all kinds of beasts in it; and We sent down water from the sky so thereby grew all kinds of refined pairs in it."
  31,11,"Allah has created this – therefore show me what has been created by those other than Him; in fact the unjust are in open error."
